verses.text_plain: Listen, O isles, unto me; and hearken, ye people, from far; The Lord hath called me from the womb; from the bowels of my mother hath he made mention of my name.
verses.verse_html: 1Listen, O isles, unto me; and hearken, ye people, from far; The Lord hath called me from the womb; from the bowels of my mother hath he made mention of my name.

verses.text_plain: And he hath made my mouth like a sharp sword; in the shadow of his hand hath he hid me, and made me a polished shaft; in his quiver hath he hid me;
verses.verse_html: 2And he hath made my mouth like a sharp sword; in the shadow of his hand hath he hid me, and made me a polished shaft; in his quiver hath he hid me;

verses.text_plain: And said unto me, Thou art my servant, O Israel, in whom I will be glorified.
verses.verse_html: 3And said unto me, Thou art my servant, O Israel, in whom I will be glorified.

tokens.text: in whom I will be glorified

verses.text_plain: Then I said, I have laboured in vain, I have spent my strength for nought, and in vain: yet surely my judgment is with the Lord, and my work with my God.
verses.verse_html:
4Then I said, I have laboured in vain, I have spent my strength for nought, and in vain: yet surely my judgment is with the Lord, and my work with my God. ▼
▼ my work: or, my reward

footnotes.body_html: ▼ my work: or, my reward

verses.text_plain: And now, saith the Lord that formed me from the womb to be his servant, to bring Jacob again to him, Though Israel be not gathered, yet shall I be glorious in the eyes of the Lord, and my God shall be my strength.
verses.verse_html:
5And now, saith the Lord that formed me from the womb to be his servant, to bring Jacob again to him, Though Israel be not gathered, yet shall I be glorious in the eyes of the Lord, and my God shall be my strength. ▼
▼ Though…: or, That Israel may be gathered to him, and I may, etc

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Though…: or, That Israel may be gathered to him, and I may, etc
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Though…: or, That Israel may be gathered to him, and I may, etc

verses.text_plain: And he said, It is a light thing that thou shouldest be my servant to raise up the tribes of Jacob, and to restore the preserved of Israel: I will also give thee for a light to the Gentiles, that thou mayest be my salvation unto the end of the earth.
verses.verse_html:
6And he said, It is a light thing that thou shouldest be my servant to raise up the tribes of Jacob, and to restore the preserved of Israel: I will also give thee for a light to the Gentiles, that thou mayest be my salvation unto the end of the earth. ▼
▼ It is…: or, Art thou lighter than that thou shouldest, etc
 , ▼
▼ preserved: or, desolations

tokens.text: that thou shouldest be my servant
that thou mayest be my salvation

footnotes.body_text: ▼ It is…: or, Art thou lighter than that thou shouldest, etc
footnotes.body_html: ▼ It is…: or, Art thou lighter than that thou shouldest, etc

verses.text_plain: Thus saith the Lord, the Redeemer of Israel, and his Holy One, to him whom man despiseth, to him whom the nation abhorreth, to a servant of rulers, Kings shall see and arise, princes also shall worship, because of the Lord that is faithful, and the Holy One of Israel, and he shall choose thee.
verses.verse_html:
7Thus saith the Lord, the Redeemer of Israel, and his Holy One, to him whom man despiseth, to him whom the nation abhorreth, to a servant of rulers, Kings shall see and arise, princes also shall worship, because of the Lord that is faithful, and the Holy One of Israel, and he shall choose thee. ▼
▼ whom man…: or, that is despised in soul

footnotes.body_text: ▼ whom man…: or, that is despised in soul
footnotes.body_html: ▼ whom man…: or, that is despised in soul

verses.text_plain: Thus saith the Lord, In an acceptable time have I heard thee, and in a day of salvation have I helped thee: and I will preserve thee, and give thee for a covenant of the people, to establish the earth, to cause to inherit the desolate heritages;
verses.verse_html:
8Thus saith the Lord, In an acceptable time have I heard thee, and in a day of salvation have I helped thee: and I will preserve thee, and give thee for a covenant of the people, to establish the earth, to cause to inherit the desolate heritages; ▼
▼ establish: or, raise up

footnotes.body_html: ▼ establish: or, raise up

verses.text_plain: That thou mayest say to the prisoners, Go forth; to them that are in darkness, Shew yourselves. They shall feed in the ways, and their pastures shall be in all high places.
verses.verse_html: 9That thou mayest say to the prisoners, Go forth; to them that are in darkness, Shew yourselves. They shall feed in the ways, and their pastures shall be in all high places.

verses.text_plain: They shall not hunger nor thirst; neither shall the heat nor sun smite them: for he that hath mercy on them shall lead them, even by the springs of water shall he guide them.
verses.verse_html: 10They shall not hunger nor thirst; neither shall the heat nor sun smite them: for he that hath mercy on them shall lead them, even by the springs of water shall he guide them.

tokens.text: them: for he that hath mercy

verses.text_plain: And I will make all my mountains a way, and my highways shall be exalted.
verses.verse_html: 11And I will make all my mountains a way, and my highways shall be exalted.

verses.text_plain: Behold, these shall come from far: and, lo, these from the north and from the west; and these from the land of Sinim.
verses.verse_html: 12Behold, these shall come from far: and, lo, these from the north and from the west; and these from the land of Sinim.

tokens.text: and, lo, these from the north

verses.text_plain: Sing, O heavens; and be joyful, O earth; and break forth into singing, O mountains: for the Lord hath comforted his people, and will have mercy upon his afflicted.
verses.verse_html: 13Sing, O heavens; and be joyful, O earth; and break forth into singing, O mountains: for the Lord hath comforted his people, and will have mercy upon his afflicted.

verses.text_plain: But Zion said, The Lord hath forsaken me, and my Lord hath forgotten me.
verses.verse_html: 14But Zion said, The Lord hath forsaken me, and my Lord hath forgotten me.

verses.text_plain: Can a woman forget her sucking child, that she should not have compassion on the son of her womb? yea, they may forget, yet will I not forget thee.
verses.verse_html:
15Can a woman forget her sucking child, that she should not have compassion on the son of her womb? yea, they may forget, yet will I not forget thee. ▼
▼ that…: Heb. from having compassion

tokens.text: that she should not have compassion

footnotes.body_html: ▼ that…: Heb. from having compassion

verses.text_plain: Behold, I have graven thee upon the palms of my hands; thy walls are continually before me.
verses.verse_html: 16Behold, I have graven thee upon the palms of my hands; thy walls are continually before me.

verses.text_plain: Thy children shall make haste; thy destroyers and they that made thee waste shall go forth of thee.
verses.verse_html: 17Thy children shall make haste; thy destroyers and they that made thee waste shall go forth of thee.

tokens.text: and they that made thee waste

verses.text_plain: Lift up thine eyes round about, and behold: all these gather themselves together, and come to thee. As I live, saith the Lord, thou shalt surely clothe thee with them all, as with an ornament, and bind them on thee, as a bride doeth.
verses.verse_html: 18Lift up thine eyes round about, and behold: all these gather themselves together, and come to thee. As I live, saith the Lord, thou shalt surely clothe thee with them all, as with an ornament, and bind them on thee, as a bride doeth.

tokens.text: thee with them all, as with an ornament

verses.text_plain: For thy waste and thy desolate places, and the land of thy destruction, shall even now be too narrow by reason of the inhabitants, and they that swallowed thee up shall be far away.
verses.verse_html: 19For thy waste and thy desolate places, and the land of thy destruction, shall even now be too narrow by reason of the inhabitants, and they that swallowed thee up shall be far away.

tokens.text: shall even now be too narrow
and they that swallowed thee up

verses.text_plain: The children which thou shalt have, after thou hast lost the other, shall say again in thine ears, The place is too strait for me: give place to me that I may dwell.
verses.verse_html: 20The children which thou shalt have, after thou hast lost the other, shall say again in thine ears, The place is too strait for me: give place to me that I may dwell.

tokens.text: which thou shalt have, after thou hast lost
to me that I may dwell

verses.text_plain: Then shalt thou say in thine heart, Who hath begotten me these, seeing I have lost my children, and am desolate, a captive, and removing to and fro? and who hath brought up these? Behold, I was left alone; these, where had they been?
verses.verse_html: 21Then shalt thou say in thine heart, Who hath begotten me these, seeing I have lost my children, and am desolate, a captive, and removing to and fro? and who hath brought up these? Behold, I was left alone; these, where had they been?

tokens.text: me these, seeing I have lost my children

verses.text_plain: Thus saith the Lord God, Behold, I will lift up mine hand to the Gentiles, and set up my standard to the people: and they shall bring thy sons in their arms, and thy daughters shall be carried upon their shoulders.
verses.verse_html:
22Thus saith the Lord God, Behold, I will lift up mine hand to the Gentiles, and set up my standard to the people: and they shall bring thy sons in their arms, and thy daughters shall be carried upon their shoulders. ▼
▼ arms: Heb. bosom

verses.text_plain: And kings shall be thy nursing fathers, and their queens thy nursing mothers: they shall bow down to thee with their face toward the earth, and lick up the dust of thy feet; and thou shalt know that I am the Lord: for they shall not be ashamed that wait for me.
verses.verse_html:
23And kings shall be thy nursing fathers, and their queens thy nursing mothers: they shall bow down to thee with their face toward the earth, and lick up the dust of thy feet; and thou shalt know that I am the Lord: for they shall not be ashamed that wait for me. ▼
▼ nursing fathers: Heb. nourishers
 , ▼
▼ queens: Heb. princesses

tokens.text: for they shall not be ashamed

footnotes.body_html: ▼ nursing fathers: Heb. nourishers

verses.text_plain: Shall the prey be taken from the mighty, or the lawful captive delivered?
verses.verse_html:
24Shall the prey be taken from the mighty, or the lawful captive delivered? ▼
▼ lawful…: Heb. captivity of the just

footnotes.body_text: ▼ lawful…: Heb. captivity of the just
footnotes.body_html: ▼ lawful…: Heb. captivity of the just

verses.text_plain: But thus saith the Lord, Even the captives of the mighty shall be taken away, and the prey of the terrible shall be delivered: for I will contend with him that contendeth with thee, and I will save thy children.
verses.verse_html:
25But thus saith the Lord, Even the captives of the mighty shall be taken away, and the prey of the terrible shall be delivered: for I will contend with him that contendeth with thee, and I will save thy children. ▼
▼ captives: Heb. captivity

tokens.text: with thee, and I will save

verses.text_plain: And I will feed them that oppress thee with their own flesh; and they shall be drunken with their own blood, as with sweet wine: and all flesh shall know that I the Lord am thy Saviour and thy Redeemer, the mighty One of Jacob.
verses.verse_html:
26And I will feed them that oppress thee with their own flesh; and they shall be drunken with their own blood, as with sweet wine: and all flesh shall know that I the Lord am thy Saviour and thy Redeemer, the mighty One of Jacob. ▼
▼ sweet: or, new
